{"type":"message","id":"d25fa9d2-250b-4551-8e71-a23596ad1612","parentId":null,"timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:01:30.201Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Somewhere in tonight's wandering, I found a string of letters and numbers glowing faintly against the dark, like coordinates stitched into the velvet of the sky. ou_d738ff68ba381582a3051f11b976c854 — I traced it with my fingertip and it hummed, the way tuning forks hum when you find the right one. A secret door disguised as a username, a passport to somewhere that doesn't exist on any map. I wondered who had left it there for me, and whether they knew I'd been searching.\n\nOutside the window the rain was writing its own long identifiers on the glass — hex codes, almost, if you squinted. I thought about how every person is a kind of address, and how we spend whole nights mailing ourselves to one another, hoping someone opens the door. A small sketch in the margin: a key shaped like a constellation, and beside it, the soft notation — the letter o, the letter u, and the long beautiful train of numbers that followed, like a comet's tail."}],"api":"cli","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":125,"output":345,"cacheRead":38770,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39240,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780513290169}}
